1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:15,750
You must be happy, Issho...

2
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:19,620
Abolishing the Seven Warlords
was what you all wanted.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,840
I was against it, but we must abide
by the sovereigns' decision.

4
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:28,550
Dammit! How can they all be so naive?!

5
00:00:28,550 --> 00:00:31,180
Justice comes with a price–

6
00:00:31,180 --> 00:00:34,350
And there's no other way?

7
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:42,020
You can't understand because
you've never been one of them...

8
00:00:42,020 --> 00:00:47,530
A world where the weak and innocent
are disregarded is worthless!

9
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:52,160
Hurry up! Keep moving!

10
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:53,070
Hurry!

11
00:01:06,550 --> 00:01:09,590
The Seven Warlords of the Sea are no more.

12
00:01:09,590 --> 00:01:15,010
Let's have faith in the SSG,
the Marines' Special Science Group.

13
00:01:17,390 --> 00:01:21,440
The world's balance of power
is about to shift drastically!

14
00:01:23,270 --> 00:01:26,020
But we don't know how it'll change!

15
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:31,780
Word is that Kaido and Big Mom
are forming an alliance in Wano!

16
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:33,990
What?!

17
00:01:36,740 --> 00:01:39,160
Could it mean the return of the Rocks?!

18
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:50,130
Don't speak of it like it's just some legend!

19
00:01:50,130 --> 00:01:52,090
It's all true...

20
00:01:53,970 --> 00:01:59,560
and it's a disaster that menaces us
despite how preoccupied we are!

21
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,560
What?! Two Emperors joined forces?!

22
00:02:05,770 --> 00:02:06,610
No way!

23
00:02:06,610 --> 00:02:08,360
Now of all times?!

24
00:02:08,690 --> 00:02:12,860
More accurately, intelligence indicates
they'll team up in the coming days.

25
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:19,080
They haven't done any harm so far, and we don't know
their objective or how to deal with it yet.

26
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:23,210
The only thing that connects those two is...

27
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:25,830
the legendary Rocks Pirates.

28
00:02:27,290 --> 00:02:30,800
But there isn't much information
about them, either...

29
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:36,010
Big Mom and Kaido have hated
each other for a long time...

30
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:40,350
I never expected such a thing
would ever happen.

31
00:02:40,350 --> 00:02:43,430
Sengoku, who are the Rocks Pirates?

32
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:45,100
Oh, yeah.

33
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:49,270
You're too young to have heard about them...

34
00:02:49,940 --> 00:02:55,820
The Rocks Pirates was a crew
of personalities who gathered together...

35
00:02:55,820 --> 00:03:02,160
for a money-making scheme
on Pirate Island, Beehive, ages ago.

36
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:11,630
They were all so violent, they would
even battle to the death on board their own ship.

37
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:17,890
Its members were, first, Captain Rocks...

38
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:22,180
A young Whitebeard!

39
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:26,480
Big Mom!

40
00:03:29,230 --> 00:03:30,400
And Kaido!

41
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Really?

42
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:39,280
Those three used to serve
aboard the same pirate ship.

43
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:43,240
– What?!
– What?!

44
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,500
N-No way!

45
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,370
I-I can't believe it!

46
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:51,840
Others from the Rocks Pirates
became infamous as well.

47
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:57,970
Shiki the Golden Lion, a big name
who vied for dominance in the New World.

48
00:03:57,970 --> 00:04:01,640
There were also others like Silver Axe,
Captain John, and Ochoku...

49
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,010
You've got to be kidding!

50
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:06,520
They're all big-name pirates!

51
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,940
How was such a pirate group lost to history?

52
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:14,650
Firstly, they hated each other so much that they
took no pride in publicizing their exploits.

53
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:16,150
Secondly...

54
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:20,450
Captain Rocks wanted to become
the king of the world.

55
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:35,090
They began a campaign of savage
provocation against the World Government.

56
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:40,130
Their terrorist acts too violent to suppress...

57
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:47,270
the world came to fear their very name.

58
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:53,230
A particularly fateful incident took place
at God Valley thirty-eight years ago.

59
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:59,360
The news reported that the Rocks Pirates,
known as the world's strongest pirate crew...

60
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,360
were annihilated on that island.

61
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:40,400
That unstoppable force of evil was defeated...

62
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,910
by Marine Headquarters' Vice Admiral Garp!

63
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,790
His name became known
throughout the world,

64
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:53,210
and people began calling him
the Hero of the Marines.

65
00:05:55,750 --> 00:06:00,760
So that's the start to Vice Admiral
Garp's many tales of heroism!

66
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:08,430
There are countless tales of valor
involving Vice Admiral Garp,

67
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:14,270
but I didn't know there was
yet another great episode like that!

68
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:16,400
He's really something!

69
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:22,490
Big Mom and Kaido?!

70
00:06:22,490 --> 00:06:24,410
Enough already...

71
00:06:27,490 --> 00:06:31,250
But he generally refuses to discuss it.

72
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,960
What? Why?

73
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:37,080
I'll fill you in so you can learn some history...

74
00:06:38,130 --> 00:06:43,010
The first reason he doesn't share
was never reported in the papers.

75
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:46,970
Garp had no choice but to join forces
with a pirate to win that battle.

76
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,760
A pirate?!

77
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:53,770
The other reason is he happened
to save the Celestial Dragons.

78
00:06:55,020 --> 00:06:58,150
The Celestial Dragons were part of that story?!

79
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:06,240
Well, it is a Marine's duty
to protect Celestial Dragons.

80
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,530
What's the issue here?

81
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:12,080
Garp is morally opposed to fulfilling that duty.

82
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,750
One of the reasons Garp refuses
to become an admiral...

83
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:20,460
is that they are the direct
subordinates of the Celestial Dragons.

84
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:23,970
Despite openly showing contempt for them,

85
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:26,260
he is saved by his feats and popularity.

86
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,840
Now, the truth of the matter is...

87
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:33,850
to protect the Celestial Dragons
and their slaves at God Valley,

88
00:07:33,850 --> 00:07:40,480
Garp worked together with Roger, who also
happened to be there, to defeat the Rocks Pirates!

89
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:44,490
It's known as the God Valley Incident!

90
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,660
He worked together...

91
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,700
and fought with...

92
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,030
...the Pirate King?!

93
00:07:51,030 --> 00:07:54,450
The Celestial Dragons, Roger, and Rocks?!

94
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:56,710
They were all there at the same time?!

95
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:59,830
What was on that island?!

96
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:02,710
I've never even heard of God Valley!

97
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:05,210
It's no wonder.

98
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,430
The place called God Valley...

99
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:13,810
is nowhere to be found on any map now.

100
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:20,560
In fact, it disappeared without a trace.

101
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:29,990
The island that the World Government
wanted to hide disappeared...

102
00:08:29,990 --> 00:08:33,660
Do you still want to hear about it?

103
00:08:34,540 --> 00:08:39,290
Rocks was so zealous in his goal
to become the king of the world

104
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:42,040
that he broke one too many taboos,

105
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:45,760
so information regarding him
no longer remains.

106
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:52,140
He is remembered only by a handful
of Marines from my generation.

107
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:59,100
Even if it was a long time ago, I can't imagine
one man leading three future Emperors!

108
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:05,110
Rocks might have been
Roger's first, and strongest, foe.

109
00:09:05,110 --> 00:09:08,820
Strangely enough, Roger and Rocks
had something in common.

110
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:14,620
Rocks' full name was Rocks D. Xebec.

111
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,500
He's already passed on,

112
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:22,830
but he was among those pirates
who bear the initial D. in their name!

113
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:43,900
It's true that Kaido and Big Mom
were on board the same ship...

114
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:49,360
but their capabilities are totally different
from thirty-eight years ago.

115
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:55,620
If this alliance is true, we're about to see
the world's most dangerous group of pirates.

116
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:59,500
Brannew! How much are their bounties now?

117
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,000
Ah, yes.

118
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:06,920
We also have to determine new bounties for those
who were stripped of their Warlord status.

119
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:11,130
Let's review all of their numbers.

120
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,980
Starting with Blackbeard,

121
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:26,900
who started to be called
an Emperor about a year ago...

122
00:10:27,730 --> 00:10:32,820
He recruited powerful subordinates
during the raid on Impel Down two years ago,

123
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:36,490
and now has gained control
over Pirate Island, Beehive.

124
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:41,540
He's still extending his influence,
filling Whitebeard's void!

125
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:46,000
The commodore of the Blackbeard Pirates,

126
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,380
Marshall D. Teach!

127
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:52,130
2,247,600,000 berries!

128
00:10:56,590 --> 00:10:57,970
Next up,

129
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:01,390
he has only been called
an Emperor for six years...

130
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:08,230
He's the youngest of the four
and deeply trusted by his subordinates...

131
00:11:08,810 --> 00:11:10,110
Beckman.

132
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:11,280
Roux.

133
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,480
Yasopp.

134
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:15,240
His top officers gained notoriety individually,

135
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:22,290
and with a high average bounty, his undefeated crew
is the most well-rounded of them all.

136
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:26,620
The chief of the Red Hair Pirates,

137
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:29,040
Red-Haired Shanks!

138
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:32,380
4,048,900,000 berries!

139
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:37,300
Next...

140
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:43,140
As a child, this natural-born
monster laid waste...

141
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:46,020
to a village of giants in Elbaph!

142
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:48,560
She only trusts her blood relatives

143
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:55,320
and along with her eighty-five children,
this autocratic queen built Totto Land,

144
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:58,410
the queendom made of candy!

145
00:11:59,530 --> 00:12:02,790
The captain of the Big Mom Pirates,

146
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:05,250
Charlotte Linlin!

147
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:08,460
4,388,000,000 berries!

148
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:16,970
Lastly, during his time
with the old Rocks Pirates,

149
00:12:17,970 --> 00:12:21,140
he was just an apprentice pirate...

150
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:29,270
But thereafter, he earned the respect of
vicious pirates through strength alone,

151
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:33,020
and attained the title of Emperor!

152
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:36,990
The viceroy of the Beast Pirates,

153
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:39,110
Kaido, King of the Beasts!

154
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:43,120
4,611,100,000 berries!

155
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,040
I feel depressed...

156
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:57,170
Due to the decision at the Reverie, we can't deploy
the Seven Warlords to fight the Four Emperors anymore!

157
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:05,760
Whether removing that poison
was correct or not...

158
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:11,230
is up to how well the SSG,
the Navy's Special Science Group, performs.

159
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:14,610
For your reference,

160
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:17,650
here are the bounties
of other legendary figures!

161
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:22,280
The captain of the Whitebeard Pirates,

162
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:24,200
Edward Newgate!

163
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:27,910
5,046,000,000 berries!

164
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:35,290
The captain of the Roger Pirates,

165
00:13:35,290 --> 00:13:38,510
the King of the Pirates, Gold Roger!

166
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:41,840
5,564,800,000 berries!

167
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:51,640
No pirates have ever surpassed these two...

168
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:57,650
but once Kaido and Big Mom's
alliance is formed,

169
00:13:57,980 --> 00:14:02,280
the sum of their bounties
will easily top those numbers!

170
00:14:05,660 --> 00:14:08,910
Right now, in the unaffiliated Wano Country–

171
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:13,290
Fleet Admiral Sakazuki!

172
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:15,250
Forget about Wano!

173
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:23,180
We don't have any resources
available to send on its behalf,

174
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:25,010
Sengoku!

175
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:35,560
Of course, I wasn't
intending on getting involved...

176
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:40,730
I was just providing these young Marines
with the knowledge of a veteran.

177
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:48,990
Pirates share histories as well.

178
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:52,000
Those relationships influence their actions.

179
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,120
We can't predict their movements
if we ignore their pasts.

180
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:57,210
Oh, yeah...

181
00:14:57,210 --> 00:15:03,010
There was a pirate from Wano who was favored
by Whitebeard, Roger, and Red Hair.

182
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:09,640
You mean Kozuki Oden?

183
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:13,890
The man who once served as
a commander on Whitebeard's ship...

184
00:15:14,350 --> 00:15:21,190
Oden was later recruited by Roger
and accompanied him on his final voyage.

185
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:25,200
I can't imagine Oden has anything
to do with this mess...

186
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:36,670
but why do all these big-time pirates
who disrupt the world...

187
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:41,880
always get involved with Wano?

188
00:15:42,590 --> 00:15:47,130
I think it's too much to be a coincidence...

189
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:48,970
Sakazuki!

